@page "/developer-blog"

<PageTitle>Developer Blog — HMGHIP</PageTitle>

<div class="stub-page">
    <div class="stub-hero">
        <div class="stub-icon">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M9.4 16.6L4.8 12l4.6-4.6L8 6l-6 6 6 6 1.4-1.4zm5.2 0l4.6-4.6-4.6-4.6L16 6l6 6-6 6-1.4-1.4z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h1 class="stub-title">Developer Blog</h1>
        <p class="stub-lead">Behind the scenes of building HMGHIP — what's new, what's next, and how it all works.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stub-body">
        <div class="stub-card">
            <h2 class="stub-section-title">Latest: The Big Polish Update</h2>
            <p>This release made the whole app real. Discover now browses the full RAWG catalog with genre filters, Game News pulls live release data, the Reviews feed shows your actual reviews next to your friends', and Top 3 picks from your own library. Every game tile in the app now opens the same action popup — Want to Play, Playing, Finished, Review.</p>
            <p>Also new: remove games from your library, filter it by status, and guest sessions that survive a refresh.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="stub-card">
            <h2 class="stub-section-title">What's Next</h2>
            <ul class="stub-list">
                <li>Real friends — follow people and see their actual activity</li>
                <li>Review comments and likes that persist</li>
                <li>Year-in-review stats page</li>
                <li>Push notifications for releases on your Want to Play list</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="stub-card">
            <h2 class="stub-section-title">Tech Stack</h2>
            <p>HMGHIP is a Blazor WebAssembly PWA — all C#, no JavaScript framework. MudBlazor handles the component layer, Firebase covers Google sign-in and per-user data in Firestore, and the RAWG Video Games Database supplies the catalog of 800,000+ games and their cover art. It deploys to GitHub Pages on every push.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
